        "content": "<p>What is the symbol <code>:=</code> called?</p>\n<p>I am learning that it signals a proof justification to the right of the statement to the left, but I don't know what it itself would be called.</p>",
        "id": 444031752,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1718119774
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Assignment. It is used both for proofs and for values (when you define a function).</p>",
